10: With this, we are now friends!
17:
Works for me. You won't mind taking
us to Gramp Zigza, yeah?
23:
Of course not! I shall show you the
way, my companions!
30:
An editor? You must be outta your
mind! Now scram!
35: What?! Surely we can talk about this!
40:
Forget it! Ain't nothing I hate more
than someone thinking they're an
expert and giving their opinion!
43:
My art's dangerous? Sounds to me
like you're just jealous that I'm good
at what I do!
48:
I swear I'm telling the truth! If you
continue as you have been until
now... people could get hurt!
52:
I pour my soul into my art... and you
expect me to let some greenhorn
get her grubby hands on it? Keep
dreaming! Now LEAVE!
59:
That is NOT how you talk to a
perfectly nice, young lady, Master!
63: Yeowch! What's the big idea, Ryouki?!
67:
That's my line! Just who taught you
this was an okay way to treat
guests?!
70:
Sorry about that! My master needs
to work on his manners.
72:
I'm Ryouki. Ryouki Kochi. I've been
studying under Master for a bit, as
his disciple!
77: I am Stella. This is Kugui.
81:
Sweet. So what's all this ruckus
about?
86:
The Diviners' Commission, huh...
Yeah, this could be bad.
90: Ryouki, I didn't take you for a coward!
95:
It's not cowardly to take advice, you
old geezer!
96:
Besides, you should be a bit more
concerned! If what she's saying is
true, then this could really sour
relations between people and yokai!
101:
Gramp Zigza... I may not be an
expert like you, but I can assure you I
have experience painting. Here...
105:
I love the Yokai Encyclopedia. The
yokai inside are so well done, they
look like they could come alive...
Which is unfortunately the root of
the problem.
107:
But that's why I wish to ensure that
this book can be enjoyed by
everyone, without putting anybody
in danger.
115:
Did you really paint this? You've got
some serious skill!
119:
I-I appreciate the sentiment, but I'm
still only a novice...
124:
Novice, schmovice! Master, we have
to let her help! I wanna see more of
her art!
129:
But... I... I'm just supposed to be an
editor...
134:
...Hmm. All right. You want her so
bad? You better be prepared to
commit to this, Ryouki.
137:
You. You've piqued my disciple's
interestand now even my own.
Let's see how far a greenhorn like
you can go.
140:
Defeat Ryouki, and I'll let you help
with the encyclopedia!
144: Defeat... Do you want us to fight?
148:
Yes, but with your art! We're gonna
have ourselves a little festival.
150:
You both have a week to produce
the best piece of yokai art you've
ever painted! And if you manage to
impress me, I'll let you edit all you
want!
155:
Oooh, sounds fun! I'm in! How about
you, Kugui?
160:
...I am as well. I can't afford to
disappoint the Chairman!
165:
Ryouki! Spend the week practicing
with the greenhorn! Your yokai art
can use the work.
167:
This is a test of skill between the East
and the West! Let the festivities
begin!
172:
Not gonna lie, it's kind of
embarrassing to be showing off my
art like this.
180:
Yeah, it's got this playful, lively
aspect to it. I'm into it.
184:
Painting's fun for me, so I guess
some of that fun seeps into my art.
You know what I'm talking about,
right, Kugui?
190:
Hm? Oh, yes, right, your work is very
well done. I like it a lot.
196:
But I was talking about MAKING art.
It's fun for you too, isn't it?
202:
Hello, everyone? Are you ready yet?
Shirano is here!
207:
Even though I'm seeing it for the first
time... There's something familiar
about that painting. This shouldn't
be possible...
213:
Princess Inaho has briefed me on
the situation. I will serve as a guide
to the yokai you will study.
215:
But that is the extent of my role. I
cannot bend the will of yokai to
yours. Are you prepared?
219:
Hehehe, here they come. Do your
best.
223:
Oh, come on! I knew this was going
to happen!
